Jeff Wicks, News24Loaded AK47 magazine. (iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - Three men have been killed and a fourth badly wounded in a shooting on the R74 near KwaMaphumulo on Wednesday night.&nbsp;It is understood that the men were gunned down by men using automatic weapons. Spent cartridges from an AK47 were found at the scene.&nbsp;Two independent sources who spoke to News24 on condition of anonymity said the shooting may have been related to taxi violence in the region.&nbsp;Police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said police officers were on the scene and investigations were underway.&nbsp;She would not be drawn into commenting on the circumstances surrounding the shooting.&nbsp;This is a developing story. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.